Here is the complete, precise trace of the event handler chain from API server watch events to informer cache updates, with exact function signatures, file paths, and data flow at every layer.

---

## Complete Event Handler Chain: API Server Watch → Informer Cache

### Architecture Overview

```
API Server (HTTP/2 chunked stream)
    │
    ▼
[Layer 1] HTTP Transport + Wire Decoding
    rest/request.go          Request.Watch() → watchInternal() → newStreamWatcher()
    rest/watch/decoder.go    Decoder.Decode()
    apimachinery/watch/streamwatcher.go  StreamWatcher.receive() goroutine
    apimachinery/watch/watch.go          watch.Interface / watch.Event
    │
    ▼  chan watch.Event
[Layer 2] Reflector (ListerWatcher → DeltaFIFO bridge)
    tools/cache/listwatch.go   ListWatch.Watch()
    tools/cache/reflector.go   Reflector.Run() → ListAndWatch() → watch() → handleWatch() → handleAnyWatch()
    │
    ▼  DeltaFIFO.Add/Update/Delete
[Layer 3] DeltaFIFO Queue
    tools/cache/delta_fifo.go  queueActionInternalLocked() → cond.Broadcast()
    │
    ▼  Pop(processDeltas)
[Layer 4] Controller dispatch loop
    tools/cache/controller.go  controller.processLoop() → processDeltas()
    │
    ▼  handler.OnAdd/OnUpdate/OnDelete
[Layer 5] SharedIndexInformer + sharedProcessor fan-out
    tools/cache/shared_informer.go  HandleDeltas() → OnAdd/OnUpdate/OnDelete → distribute()
    │
    ▼  processorListener.addCh
[Layer 6] Per-listener goroutine pair (pop + run)
    tools/cache/shared_informer.go  processorListener.pop() → processorListener.run()
    │
    ▼
Registered ResourceEventHandler.OnAdd/OnUpdate/OnDelete (user code)
```

