### Layer 5 — SharedIndexInformer: Cache Update + Fan-out

**File:** `client-go--v0.32.0/tools/cache/shared_informer.go`

`sharedIndexInformer.Run()` sets `Process: s.HandleDeltas` in the controller config:

```go
func (s *sharedIndexInformer) Run(stopCh <-chan struct{}) {
    fifo := NewDeltaFIFOWithOptions(DeltaFIFOOptions{
        KnownObjects:          s.indexer,   // cache.Store used as knownObjects
        EmitDeltaTypeReplaced: true,
        Transformer:           s.transform,
    })
    cfg := &Config{
        Queue:         fifo,
        ListerWatcher: s.listerWatcher,
        Process:       s.HandleDeltas,   // ← the Pop callback
        // ...
    }
    s.controller = New(cfg)
    // ...
    wg.StartWithChannel(processorStopCh, s.processor.run)  // starts listener goroutines
    s.controller.Run(stopCh)
}
```

`HandleDeltas` is the `Process` callback invoked by `processLoop → Pop`:

```go
// HandleDeltas: called by controller.processLoop() for each Deltas batch.
// Holds blockDeltas lock to prevent AddEventHandler races.
func (s *sharedIndexInformer) HandleDeltas(obj interface{}, isInInitialList bool) error {
    s.blockDeltas.Lock()
    defer s.blockDeltas.Unlock()
    if deltas, ok := obj.(Deltas); ok {
        return processDeltas(s, s.indexer, deltas, isInInitialList)
        //                   ↑ s implements ResourceEventHandler via OnAdd/OnUpdate/OnDelete
        //                              ↑ s.indexer is the cache.Store (threadSafeMap)
    }
    return errors.New("object given as Process argument is not Deltas")
}
```

`processDeltas` calls back into `s.OnAdd/OnUpdate/OnDelete`:

```go
// OnAdd: updates mutation detector, then distributes addNotification to all listeners
func (s *sharedIndexInformer) OnAdd(obj interface{}, isInInitialList bool) {
    s.cacheMutationDetector.AddObject(obj)
    s.processor.distribute(addNotification{newObj: obj, isInInitialList: isInInitialList}, false)
}

// OnUpdate: detects resync (same ResourceVersion = no real change) to limit fan-out
func (s *sharedIndexInformer) OnUpdate(old, new interface{}) {
    isSync := accessor(new).GetResourceVersion() == accessor(old).GetResourceVersion()
    s.cacheMutationDetector.AddObject(new)
    s.processor.distribute(updateNotification{oldObj: old, newObj: new}, isSync)
}

// OnDelete: distributes deleteNotification
func (s *sharedIndexInformer) OnDelete(old interface{}) {
    s.processor.distribute(deleteNotification{oldObj: old}, false)
}
```

`sharedProcessor.distribute` fans out to every registered listener:

```go
// distribute: sends notification to all listeners (or only syncing ones for sync events)
func (p *sharedProcessor) distribute(obj interface{}, sync bool) {
    p.listenersLock.RLock()
    defer p.listenersLock.RUnlock()
    for listener, isSyncing := range p.listeners {
        switch {
        case !sync:       listener.add(obj)  // all listeners get non-sync events
        case isSyncing:   listener.add(obj)  // only syncing listeners get sync events
        // else: skip
        }
    }
}
```

