### Key Design Properties

| Property | Mechanism |
|---|---|
| **Ordering** | `DeltaFIFO.queue []string` is a strict FIFO; `Pop()` processes one key at a time under lock |
| **Delta accumulation** | Multiple rapid changes to the same key are coalesced into one `Deltas` slice; consumer sees full history |
| **Cache consistency** | `processDeltas` updates `s.indexer` before calling `OnAdd/OnUpdate/OnDelete`; cache is always current when handler fires |
| **Fan-out isolation** | Each `ResourceEventHandler` has its own `processorListener` with independent ring buffer; a slow handler cannot block others |
| **Resync vs real update** | `OnUpdate` with identical `ResourceVersion` sets `isSync=true`; `distribute` skips non-syncing listeners |
| **Panic safety** | `processorListener.run()` wraps handler calls in `wait.Until` with 1s recovery; panicking handlers skip one notification but continue |
| **Backpressure** | `processorListener.pendingNotifications` is an unbounded `RingGrowing`; a stalled handler accumulates memory but never blocks the informer |
| **Watch reconnect** | `Reflector.watch()` loop: on any error, `w.Stop(); w = nil`; next iteration opens a fresh watch from `LastSyncResourceVersion` |

